From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-21)
Subject: [PATCH] hooks: add "octo" to InternalHookEventType union

Extend the central hook event-type union in src/hooks/internal-hooks.ts
with a new "octo" literal so that Octopus Orchestrator lifecycle events
(mission.create, arm.spawn, arm.completed) can flow through the
existing internal hook dispatcher without any runtime changes.

This is a vocabulary-only change. The dispatcher machinery
(registerInternalHook, triggerInternalHook, hasInternalHookListeners,
createInternalHookEvent) is generic over the event type and requires
no behavioral changes. Dispatch call sites that fire octo.* events
land in the Octopus control-plane code in a later PR; this PR opens
the door in the central union so those call sites type-check.

No behavior change for deployments with octo.enabled: false (default
through Milestone 1). When octo is disabled, no producers exist, so
the new event family is dead code at the hook layer.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

